Usage: InstallFusion.sh [OPTIONS]

Used for the creation of Fusion services utilizing searchhub with AWS services
   -f | --fusion_home [PATH]
				Set desired Fusion home directory, if not set
				this will default to: /home/<username>/fusion/4.1.0
   -h | --help			Displays help
   -H | --hostname [HOSTNAME]
				Set the hostname that will be used for SSH and SCP protocalls
   -i | --identity [IDENTITY FILE]
				Set the identity file that will be used for SSH and SCP protocalls
   -s | --searchhub_home [PATH] 	
				Set desired SearchHub home directory, if not set
				this will default to: /home/<username>/src/lucidworks/searchhub
   -u | --username [USERNAME]
				Set the username that will be used for SSH and SCP protocalls,
				as well as Fusion/SearchHub home directories

The hostname, username, and indentity_file flags are required due to the dependancies of SSH and SCP,
otherwise all other flags have default variables set.
 

Examples:	./InstallFusion.sh -i foobar.pem -u ubuntu -H ec2-11-111-111-111.compute-1.amazonaws.com
		./InstallFusion.sh --identity foobar.pem --username ubuntu --hostname ec2-11-111-111-111.compute-1.amazonaws.com
		./InstallFusion.sh -i foobar.pem -u ubuntu -H ec2-11-111-111-111.compute-1.amazonaws.com -f /home/ubuntu/fusion/4.1.0 -s /home/ubuntu/src/lucidworks/searchhub
